article.headline: CS Bakersfield 69, Utah Valley St. 60
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Donavan Bragg scored 12 of his 15 points in the second half, leading a balanced Cal State Bakersfield attack in a 69-60 win over Utah Valley Saturday. Trent Blakley scored a team-high 16 points for the Roadrunners (6-15), while Alex Johnson had 14 and Santwon Latunde had 11 points and a game-high 10 rebounds. Utah Valley's Ryan Toolson, who scored a career-high 63 points in a quadruple overtime win at Chicago State Thursday, netted a team-high 22, while Josh Olson chipped in 15. Down 30-27 at the break, Bakersfield reeled off nine unanswered points midway through the second period to turn a two-point lead into a 61-50 advantage with 5:24 remaining. Jordan Swarbrick cut the Utah Valley (10-9) deficit to eight with a three at the 54-second mark, but Bragg and Johnson each nailed a pair of free throws to push the lead back to double digits.
